nodes.title: Info Workflow
widgets_values: If the Load Image group is switched on, the sizes for generation are approximated to the loaded image, or you can select a new size at the top, in which case the image will be cropped. For pure text to image, you can set the size directly in the Base Settings, but the Load Image group must be switched off. Inpaint works the same as for image to image. You can also combine both, but please note that the Load Image switch is not switched off when you switch off Image to Image, although this deactivates the Load image group. Little Bug in den Custom Nodes.

nodes.title: Model Sampling Flux Infos
widgets_values:
How the ModelSamplingFlux Parameters Work Together:

Max Shift sets the possible maximum flexibility. Standard 1.15
Base Shift sets the starting flexibility. Standard 0.50

Summary:
High Shift: More potential for adding new details and sharpness, but with an increased risk of noise and artifacts.
Low Shift: More controlled and potentially cleaner images with less risk of noise, but possibly less detail and sharpness.

CLIPTextEncodeFlux:
1.02.0 Very weak guidance 
 Model ignores parts of the prompt. Abstract art, experiments.
2.53.5 Balanced 
 Slight stylization, but recognizable prompt implementation. 
Standard for Flux (e.g., landscapes).
4.05.0 Strong guidance 
 More precise details, but less "artistic flow." 
Legible text, clear objects.
> 5.0 Overfitting risk 
 Unnaturally hard edges/artifacts. Only for special cases (e.g., logos).
